"""Binary struct parser — xxd-style output with ANSI color highlighting.

Reads a byte stream from stdin, parses it as repetitions of a C struct using
hachoir, then renders a coloured hex dump with each field highlighted.

C struct (Entry, 16 bytes, little-endian)::

    uint32_t id;          4 B — record identifier
    uint32_t timestamp;   4 B — epoch seconds
    uint16_t type;        2 B — record type
    uint16_t value;       2 B — data value
    uint8_t  flag;        1 B — flag bits
    uint8_t  reserved[3]; 3 B — padding

Input that is not a multiple of 16 bytes has the trailing bytes rendered
as raw (un-highlighted).
"""

